  "ciliary_role": "Also known as ICK. Regulator of ciliary transport through regulation of BBS proteins and IFT-B localisation. Loss of ICK causes accumulation of IFT-A, IFT-B, and BBSome components at the ciliary tips. It is a Kif3a ki se  essential for proper ciliogenesis (24797473, 25243405). Involved in the negative control of ciliary length, abnormal ICK function results in the mislocalisation of key mediators for Shh (24853502, 25243405). Anterograde tafficking of CILK is essential for retrograde IFT (32732286)",
